data.title: Monica Seles Biography
data.meta_description: Read all about Monica Seles with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

Moved with her family to the United States from Yugoslavia in 1986; she enrolled in the Nick Bollettieri Tennis Academy in Florida

Won her first pro singles title in 1989 by defeating Chris Evert in the final of a tournament in Houston

Became, in 1990, the youngest woman to win the French Open, at 16

Perfected two-handed grip on the racket, which was later emulated by many women players

Ranked the No

1 professional woman's tennis player in the world in 1991 and 1992

Was stabbed in the back in April 1993 during a match in Germany by a mentally ill man who claimed to be a fan of Steffi Graf

Seles was out of tennis for more than two years as a result of the attack

Won nine career Grand Slam titles

Won 53 singles titles and six doubles titles in her career

Retired in February 2008

Was the first celebrity eliminated in Season 6 of ABC's Dancing With the Stars, where she was paired with pro Jonathan Roberts
